### user-permissions.http
###
### User Permission Management API scenarios
### Tests for viewing and updating user permissions
###
### Usage: Use with IntelliJ HTTP Client or similar tools
### Requires: Variable `apiBaseUrl` defined in http-client.env.json
### Note: These endpoints require MEMBERS:PERMISSIONS authority
###

### Test 1: Get user permissions
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Accept: application/hal+json

### Expected: 200 OK with user's authorities list
### Note: Replace UUID with actual user ID from your database

###

### Test 2: Get user permissions - invalid UUID format
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/invalid-uuid/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Accept: application/hal+json

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - invalid UUID format

###

### Test 3: Get user permissions - user not found
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Accept: application/hal+json

### Expected: 404 Not Found - user doesn't exist

###

### Test 4: Update user permissions - grant all permissions
PUT {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorities": [
    "MEMBERS:CREATE",
    "MEMBERS:READ",
    "MEMBERS:UPDATE",
    "MEMBERS:DELETE",
    "MEMBERS:PERMISSIONS"
  ]
}

### Expected: 200 OK with updated permissions
### Note: Replace UUID with actual user ID from your database

###

### Test 5: Update user permissions - read-only access
PUT {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorities": [
    "MEMBERS:READ"
  ]
}

### Expected: 200 OK with updated permissions (read-only)

###

### Test 6: Update user permissions - create and read
PUT {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorities": [
    "MEMBERS:CREATE",
    "MEMBERS:READ"
  ]
}

### Expected: 200 OK with updated permissions

###

### Test 7: Update user permissions - empty authorities (should fail)
PUT {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorities": []
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - at least one authority required

###

### Test 8: Update user permissions - invalid authority (should fail)
PUT {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorities": [
    "INVALID:AUTHORITY"
  ]
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - invalid authority

###

### Test 9: Update user permissions - remove last admin (should fail)
PUT {{apiBaseUrl}}/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorities": [
    "MEMBERS:CREATE",
    "MEMBERS:READ",
    "MEMBERS:UPDATE",
    "MEMBERS:DELETE"
  ]
}

### Expected: 409 Conflict - cannot remove MEMBERS:PERMISSIONS from last admin
### Detail: "Cannot remove MEMBERS:PERMISSIONS: this is the last active admin user"

###

###
